trans-unit.source: The IAccPropServer and all of its exposed members are part of a managed wrapper for the Component Object Model (COM) <xref uid="langword_csharp_IAccPropServer" name="IAccPropServer" href=""></xref> interface.
For more information about IAccPropServer, see the documentation for `Dynamic Properties` in the Microsoft Active Accessibility documentation in the MSDN library at http://msdn.microsoft.com/library.

The <xref href="Accessibility.IAccPropServer"></xref> and all of its exposed members are part of a managed wrapper for the Component Object Model (COM) <xref uid="langword_csharp_IAccPropServer" name="IAccPropServer" href=""></xref> interface.

For more information about <xref:Accessibility.IAccPropServer>, see the documentation for `IAccPropServer::GetPropValue` in the Microsoft Active Accessibility documentation in the MSDN library at http://msdn.microsoft.com/library.
Contains a string that identifies the property being requested.
Specifies the length of the identity string specified by the `pIDString` parameter.
Specifies a GUID indicating the desired property.
Specifies the value of the overridden property.
This parameter is valid only if `pfHasProp` is TRUE.
The server must set this to VT_EMPTY if `pfHasProp` is set to FALSE.
Indicates whether the server is supplying a value for the requested property.
The server should set this to TRUE if it is returning an overriding property or to FALSE if it is not returning a property (in which case it should also set `pvarValue` to VT_EMPTY).
